00:12:30.283 --> 00:12:33.303
In other words, pride comes before a fall.

00:12:33.953 --> 00:12:38.413
And this fall, for Napoleon and for the country he had come to call his

00:12:38.413 --> 00:12:44.443
own, came in June of 1812, with his decision to march East, into Russia.

00:12:45.683 --> 00:12:48.913
As the French army marched into Russia, they weren’t

00:12:48.923 --> 00:12:53.083
confronted by a proud and fierce army or violent resistance.

00:12:53.533 --> 00:12:59.143
There were battles along the way, but most of all they were confronted by…nothing.

00:12:59.973 --> 00:13:05.233
The Russian army simply retreated east, drawing the French army further and further

00:13:05.443 --> 00:13:10.303
into Russia and further and further away from supplies and reinforcements in France.

00:13:11.613 --> 00:13:15.253
Along the way, the Russian army destroyed supplies that

00:13:15.253 --> 00:13:17.653
could possibly be used by the advancing French army.

00:13:18.523 --> 00:13:24.743
And when the French army arrived all the way to Moscow, almost 3,000 kilometres

00:13:24.903 --> 00:13:30.453
from Paris, they found the city not just practically deserted, but on fire.

00:13:31.884 --> 00:13:35.014
They had conquered the Russian capital but…there was

00:13:35.014 --> 00:13:38.684
nobody there and the place was burning to the ground.

00:13:39.754 --> 00:13:42.834
It’s almost like a philosophical question: have you

00:13:42.834 --> 00:13:46.204
really captured a capital city if there is nothing there?

00:13:47.666 --> 00:13:52.486
Soon enough, it became a very real question for Napoleon and his troops.

00:13:53.706 --> 00:14:00.446
On October 19th, 1812, with winter approaching, very limited supplies, a demoralised

00:14:00.616 --> 00:14:07.286
and unruly army and a long way back to Paris, the French army left the ashes of Moscow.

00:14:08.676 --> 00:14:13.036
It was still over 100,000 men strong, but these men

00:14:13.186 --> 00:14:17.326
were tired, homesick, hungry, and increasingly cold.

00:14:17.866 --> 00:14:20.876
Not exactly in prime condition for fighting.

00:14:22.256 --> 00:14:26.366
And as they started the long march back, and with the

00:14:26.396 --> 00:14:29.676
temperature dropping, their condition only worsened.

00:14:30.666 --> 00:14:34.366
Horses died of starvation or were killed for their meat.

00:14:34.826 --> 00:14:38.756
