00:15:36.453 --> 00:15:41.633
this was a tactical disaster, a colossal miscalculation.

00:15:43.103 --> 00:15:47.733
As you will know if you’ve spent much time reading about this period, or if you’ve

00:15:47.733 --> 00:15:53.163
read War and Peace, let’s say, there are countless theories and hypotheses about why

00:15:53.313 --> 00:15:58.783
Napoleon made such a miscalculation, and what could have been done to avoid this,

00:15:59.283 --> 00:16:05.553
but the end result was the worst and most humiliating military defeat of his career.

00:16:07.110 --> 00:16:12.350
A year later he would suffer another defeat at the Battle of Leipzig, against Austrian,

00:16:12.580 --> 00:16:18.290
Prussian, Swedish and Russian forces, and he would be forced to abdicate his position as

00:16:18.320 --> 00:16:23.840
Emperor of France, the monarchy was restored to France, and Napoleon was exiled to the

00:16:23.840 --> 00:16:30.000
island of Elba, a tiny island sandwiched between his homeland of Corsica and mainland Italy.

00:16:31.370 --> 00:16:36.300
This was in April of 1814, yet this was not the end for

00:16:36.300 --> 00:16:39.410
our hero, or villain, depending on your point of view.

00:16:40.370 --> 00:16:45.660
The following year he managed to escape from Elba with a small crew of 1,000 supporters.

00:16:46.060 --> 00:16:52.350
He marched on Paris, was welcomed with open arms, as the new Bourbon monarchy was not particularly

00:16:52.350 --> 00:17:00.290
well-liked, and on 20th of March 1815, he proclaimed himself Emperor of France for a second time.

00:17:01.680 --> 00:17:02.850
It wouldn’t last long.

00:17:04.070 --> 00:17:10.920
He had raised an army that numbered around 200,000, and he marched northwards to try to split up

00:17:10.930 --> 00:17:16.350
the British army, which was coming from the north, and the Prussians, who were coming from the East.

00:17:17.550 --> 00:17:22.440
This culminated, on the 18th of June, 1815, with the Battle

00:17:22.540 --> 00:17:25.320
of Waterloo, as you heard at the start of the episode.

00:17:26.490 --> 00:17:30.840
It was decisive, but not in the way Napoleon had imagined.

00:17:31.860 --> 00:17:38.039
The French army was defeated once and for all, Napoleon was forced to abdicate

00:17:38.060 --> 00:17:43.890
yet again, and on the 15th of July 1815 he surrendered to the British.

00:17:45.290 --> 00:17:49.280
The British decided to send him as far away as they possibly could,

00:17:49.620 --> 00:17:53.160
to the island of St Helena in the middle of the Atlantic Ocean.

00:17:54.320 --> 00:17:56.400
From here there was no escape.

00:17:57.270 --> 00:18:01.870
And the conditions were a far cry from the luxurious ones he had

00:18:01.870 --> 00:18:06.000
enjoyed as French Emperor at his palace in Fontainebleau, outside Paris.

00:18:06.690 --> 00:18:09.270
