00:18:26.210 --> 00:18:31.600
party had to wear military uniform, almost as if he simply didn’t want to admit

00:18:31.870 --> 00:18:36.000
that he was no longer in charge of the most powerful military force in Europe.

00:18:37.300 --> 00:18:41.990
And on the 5th of May 1821, at the age of 51, he

00:18:41.990 --> 00:18:45.440
died, with the official verdict being stomach cancer.

00:18:46.920 --> 00:18:50.780
As to his legacy, well there is a lot to unpack.

00:18:52.020 --> 00:18:55.210
We didn’t have the chance to talk about this yet, but he laid

00:18:55.220 --> 00:18:59.190
the foundations of the modern French state and its institutions.

00:18:59.740 --> 00:19:03.980
