00:19:24.090 --> 00:19:28.660
if not millions of people, he is not without his fair share of critics.

00:19:30.140 --> 00:19:34.850
He has been called “a megalomaniac who wrought greater misery than any man

00:19:34.850 --> 00:19:39.930
before the coming of Hitler”, an enabler of slavery, and a dangerous tyrant.

00:19:41.280 --> 00:19:46.640
Undeniably, had he not sent his men into Russia, hundreds of thousands of his own

00:19:46.640 --> 00:19:51.690
people’s lives would have been saved, let alone the Russian and Austrian casualties.

00:19:52.840 --> 00:19:59.830
But in France, he remains an incredibly popular character, albeit one with clear flaws.

00:20:01.290 --> 00:20:06.510
In 2021 the French president, Emanuel Macron, clearly laid out the

00:20:06.510 --> 00:20:12.630
difficulties of his legacy, saying “Napoleon was both ogre and eagle,

00:20:13.150 --> 00:20:18.510
Alexander and Nero … the soul of the world and the demon of Europe,”

00:20:20.121 --> 00:20:24.361
Whatever your view on Napoleon, it’s hard to deny that he lived an

00:20:24.361 --> 00:20:28.851
impressive life, in the literal sense of making a mark on the world.

00:20:30.241 --> 00:20:36.621
He was a man with deep convictions in his own ability, a man who believed he was unstoppable.

00:20:37.561 --> 00:20:41.951
So, we will leave this episode with a quote from Napoleon that,

00:20:42.201 --> 00:20:47.361
depending on your opinion of him, underlines his egomania or simply

00:20:47.361 --> 00:20:51.551
demonstrates the confidence that one has to have to achieve what he did.

00:20:52.911 --> 00:21:00.331
“Impossible”, he said, “is a word to be found only in the dictionary of fools”.

00:21:03.338 --> 00:21:07.958
